fields.description:
*Context*

Different tooth numbering system are used for different region, we should accommodate this to avoid confusing users
----
*Application Rules*

*[https://jira.dentsplysirona.com/browse/S3808-3181*]

System shows the tooth numbers in the desired tooth numbering system of the user depending on the {*}country of the user his company{*}:
 * If Country = United States, use tooth numbering system = UNS
 * All other countries, use tooth numbering system = FDI 

*The difference between UNS & FDI*

When DS Core lists selected tooth numbers always the same clock wise sorting is used (independent on in which order the teeth were selected in the dental chart):
 * FDI (EU/RoW): 18-11 ; 21-28 ; 38-31; 41-48

!image-2025-08-04-15-59-54-302.png!
 * UNS = US: 1-32 

!image-2025-08-04-16-01-07-977.png!
----
h2. {color:#00875a}*Rules (read me!!)*{color}
 * *Default tooth numbering system:* based on the company location of the users
 * {*}Agent Requirement -user intention identification{*}:  be able to identify the corresponding system through the text input instead of just sticking to the system default
 * {*}Conflicted scenario{*}: Agent could accept one and only one tooth numbering system at a time
 * *overwrite rules over default tooth system*
 ** User clearly command to apply the non-default tooth numbering system (FDI 11, 12 under default UNS)
 ** The stated tooth IDs is applicable to the non-default tooth numbering system (tooth # 1,2,3 under default  FDI)
 ** otherwise stick to the default system
 * *Attach FDI & UNS under each reply*
 * *The front end displays the tooth numbering system (side bar & dental card)based on identified user intention* 
 * *The front end converts tooth numbering system into FDI when submit the order*

comments.body:
Tested twice, and the result is attached.

[^tooth_number_system_single_round_20250825102018.csv]

[^tooth_number_system_single_round_20250825104958.csv]

The system is able to identify the tooth numbering system and teeth location.
In average, pass rate is 23/26, which is around 90%. 

Some insights of failed cases:

currently the extractor node seems cannot detect shade=4M, most of the failures are because of this..
